.\" claudii manual — auto-synced to wiki via GitHub Actions
.TH CLAUDII 1 "April 3, 2026" "claudii 0.22.0" "claudii manual"
.
.SH NAME
claudii \- Fast Claude Code aliases with live model status and session insights
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B claudii
.IR command " [" args ]
.PP
When invoked with no arguments,
.B claudii
shows a contextual summary: active session data, a rate-limit warning
(when 5h usage >= 80%), or a welcome message when no cache exists.
.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Quick start — enable everything at once:
.B claudii on
.TP
Live health check:
.B claudii status
.TP
Show active sessions with token throughput and rate limits:
.B claudii se
.TP
Read a config value:
.B claudii config get aliases.cl.model
.TP
Switch CC-Statusline to dense layout:
.B claudii cc-statusline preset focused
.TP
Toggle only ClaudeStatus RPROMPT:
.B claudii claudestatus off
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B claudii
is a zsh plugin and CLI for Claude Code power users:
fast aliases to launch Claude with the right model and effort,
live model health in your RPROMPT, and a metrics statusline inside Claude Code sessions.
.
.SH INSTALL
.B Homebrew (recommended):
.PP
.RS
.nf
brew tap bmmmm/tap
brew install claudii
.fi
.RE
.PP
Add to
.IR ~/.zshrc :
.RS
.nf
source "$(brew --prefix)/opt/claudii/libexec/claudii.plugin.zsh"
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Manual:
.PP
.RS
.nf
git clone https://github.com/bmmmm/claudii ~/claudii
bash ~/claudii/install.sh
.fi
.RE
.
.SH LAUNCHING CLAUDE
Shell functions for fast model access.
Configured under the
.B aliases.*
config namespace.
Auto-fallback to a healthy model when the configured model is down
.RB ( fallback.enabled ).
.TP
.B cl
Claude Sonnet, high effort. General-purpose default.
.TP
.B clo
Claude Opus, high effort. Complex tasks, server work.
.TP
.B clm
Claude Opus, xhigh effort. Hardest problems, maximum reasoning.
.TP
.B clq
Claude Sonnet, medium effort.
Launches in
.I search.dir
(default:
.IR ~/claude-search ).
Equivalent to
.BR "claudii search" .
.TP
.B clh
Show the alias table and run a live model health check.
.TP
.B clorch / cle
Example agent aliases — see
.BR "claudii agents" .
.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output structured JSON instead of formatted text.
Available for:
.BR status ", " sessions ", " cost ", " trends ", " doctor ", " version ", " agents .
.TP
.B \-\-tsv
Output tab-separated values (header + data rows).
Available for:
.BR sessions ", " cost .
.PP
When stdout is not a terminal, ANSI colors are stripped and plain text is emitted.
.B version
prints only the bare version number when piped.
.
.SH DISPLAY LAYERS
Three separate layers each serve a different scope:
.TP
.B ClaudeStatus (RPROMPT)
Model health indicators in the right-hand shell prompt.
Reads a local cache — no network calls in
.IR precmd .
Indicators:
.B \(dg
= ok,
.B \(ti
= degraded,
.B \(da
= down,
.B ?
= unreachable,
.B \(lB\(el\(rB
= loading,
.B \(rn
= refreshing.
.br
A trailing incident glyph mirrors status.claude.com:
.B \[u203C]
investigating,
.B \[u2690]
identified,
.B \[u25CE]
monitoring \(em stage-colored when a tracked model is actually affected.
When an incident exists but none of your tracked models are affected (e.g. a
note about models you don't use), it shows a neutral
.B \[u24D8]
instead of an alarm.
.TP
.B Session Dashboard (above prompt)
Per-session summary lines above the prompt, rendered via the precmd hook.
Shows model, context %, cost, 5h rate limit + countdown.
Only shown after
.B claudii
commands; suppressed after
.BR se / si / sessions .
.TP
.B CC-Statusline (inside Claude Code)
Metrics line inside Claude Code sessions via the
.B statusLine
hook in
.IR ~/.claude/settings.json .
Receives live JSON from Claude Code on each turn.
Segments configured via
.B statusline.lines
(see
.BR CONFIGURATION ).
.PP
Data flow:
.RS
.nf
Claude Code \(-> CC-Statusline (stdin JSON) \(-> cache \(-> Session Dashboard
                                            \(-> history-YYYY-MM.tsv
.fi
.RE
.
.SH COMMANDS
.
.SS Overview (bare claudii)
Running
.B claudii
with no arguments prints the Overview: a modular status page built from
sections. Default order: account (rate limits + today's cost), sessions
(active/inactive/stale counts, next cron wake, bg tasks), activity
(mini vibemap strip), agents (configured agents grouped by model tier,
plus shell aliases), services (ClaudeStatus / Dashboard / CC-Statusline
state), commands (grouped quick reference).
.PP
Section order and selection are config-driven via
.B overview.sections
(array of section names) \(em remove a name to hide that section,
reorder the array to reorder the output. Unknown names render an
inline warning instead of failing.
.PP
Dim lines starting with \(->\& list invocable commands only \(em
never data.
.
.SS Display Layer Control
.TP
.B on
Enable all three layers at once (ClaudeStatus, Session Dashboard, CC-Statusline).
.TP
.B off
Disable all three layers at once.
.TP
.BR "claudestatus " [on|off]
Toggle only the ClaudeStatus RPROMPT.
Without argument: show current state.
.TP
.BR "session-dashboard " [on|off]
Toggle only the Session Dashboard above the prompt.
Without argument: show current state.
Deprecated alias:
.BR dashboard .
.TP
.BR "cc-statusline " [on|off]
Toggle only the CC-Statusline inside Claude Code.
Modifies
.IR ~/.claude/settings.json .
Without argument: show current state.
.TP
.BI "cc-statusline preset " [name]
Switch the CC-Statusline layout to a named preset.
Without a name, lists available presets.
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B focused
\(em dense 3-line layout: identity / metrics / env.
.IP \(bu 2
.B calm
\(em bare 2-line layout: model / context-bar.
.IP \(bu 2
.B default
\(em restore the shipped 5-line layout.
.RE
.IP
After switching, restart Claude Code to see the change.
Writes
.B statusline.lines
to
.IR config.json .
.TP
.BR "insomnii " [on|off|auto|status|install]
Manage the optional
.BR cc-insomnii (1)
bedtime clock segment.
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B on
\(em require delegation; doctor warns if the binary is missing.
.IP \(bu 2
.B off
\(em suppress delegation; the clock segment is empty.
.IP \(bu 2
.B auto
\(em delegate when installed, skip when not (default).
.IP \(bu 2
.B status
(or no argument) \(em show binary path and active mode.
.IP \(bu 2
.B install
\(em clone
.B $CC_INSOMNII_REPO
(default
.IR https://github.com/bmmmm/cc-insomnii )
and run its
.BR install.sh .
Idempotent.
.RE
.TP
.B explain
Component overview with current status, data flow, and symbol legend.
Aliases:
.BR layers ", " components .
.
.SS Model Health (ClaudeStatus)
.TP
.B status
Live model health check (bypasses cache).
Per-model status table with icons, last-check time, active incidents, and
recent state transitions (from the status history log).
Absolute timestamps honor
.BR display.timezone .
Supports
.BR \-\-json .
Alias:
.BR s .
.TP
.BR "status " 5m|15m|30m|60m
Set the base background cache refresh interval (default: 15m).
Values below 30s are rejected.
The effective interval adapts to the last known state: 2\(mu base while
healthy, base\(di5 (min 60s) during incidents, base when the status API is
unreachable.
.TP
.BR "status \-\-history " [\-\-days\ N]
Print the full model-state transition log from
.IR status-history.tsv ,
newest first (bare
.B status
shows only the last 5).
.B \-\-days\ N
limits output to transitions within the last
.I N
days.
Absolute timestamps honor
.BR display.timezone .
Supports
.BR \-\-json .
.
.SS Sessions and Cost
.TP
.B sessions
List active and recent sessions: model, context %, token throughput with
cache-hit rate, rate limits, worktree, agent context, and a fingerprint of
top-5 files accessed. Cost is no longer in this view \(em see
.BR cost .
Background sessions
.RB ( "claude --bg" )
are marked
.BR [bg] .
Supports
.BR \-\-json " and " \-\-tsv .
Aliases:
.BR se ", " ss .
.TP
.BI "sessions \-\-resume " id
Resume a session by ID.
Equivalent to
.BR "claude --resume " id .
.TP
.B sessions-inactive
Inactive (ended or stale) sessions with age, context, and rate-limit data.
Shows badges: pinned, stale, or idle.
Alias:
.BR si .
.TP
.BI "session " session-id
Per-session drilldown from the insights cache, matched by session-id substring
(first match wins). Shows the token split (input / output / cache write as share
bars, plus cache read with its hit rate and the thinking-block count), the
top tools with per-tool error markers, and compact lines for subagents, stop
reasons, and rate-limit hits (account-wide). Live context %, model, and project
come from the
.I session-*
cache when one still exists; for ended sessions the model is inferred from the
token data and the context bar is omitted.
Protect an inactive session from garbage collection.
Matches by session ID substring (first match wins).
.TP
.BI "unpin " session-id
Remove GC protection from a pinned session.
.TP
.B gc
Remove stale session cache files.
Pinned sessions are never removed.
Run
.B claudii si
to inspect before garbage collecting.
With
.BI "\-\-insights " DAYS
additionally prunes orphaned insights caches (sessions whose source transcript
Claude Code already deleted) older than
.I DAYS
days.
Dry-run by default \(em add
.B \-\-yes
to delete.
Orphaned caches are the only cost history beyond Claude Code's transcript
retention; caches whose transcript still exists are never touched.
Alias:
.BR g .
.TP
.BI "resume " session-id
Resume a session by ID
.RB ( "claude --resume " id ).
Use
.B claudii se
to list IDs.
.TP
.B cost
The dollar view (token throughput lives in the other commands). Per-period spend
with a per-tier breakdown: Today and Week show share bars sorted by amount plus
the period token total; Months and Years render as a column matrix (model tiers
\(mu periods) with row and column totals. Reads from
.I ~/.cache/claudii/history-YYYY-MM.tsv
(written by the CC-Statusline handler).
Supports
.BR \-\-json " and " \-\-tsv .
Alias:
.BR c .
.TP
.B skills-cost
Per-skill (or per-plugin, per-MCP-tool) cost breakdown using attribution data
from
.BR claudii-insights .
Shows calls, total cost, average cost per call, the dominant model
(the model behind \[>=]80% of a row's attributed calls, otherwise
.BR mixed ),
and an outlier flag
.RB ( ! )
when a row's average is \[>=]2\[mu] the median with at least 10 calls.
Subagent usage counts toward the skill that spawned the agent.
.RS
.TP
.BI "\-\-days " N
Rolling window (default 30). Passed to
.BR "claudii-insights merge" .
.TP
.BI "\-\-compare " BEFORE : AFTER
Trend comparison of two windows: the prior period
.RI "[now\-(" BEFORE + AFTER "), now\-" AFTER ")"
against the recent
.RI "[now\-" AFTER ", now]"
\(em e.g.
.B "\-\-compare 30:30"
is the previous 30 days vs the last 30.
The headline metric is
.BR out-tokens/call ,
which (unlike $/call) does not scale with session context size, so it isolates
whether a skill talks less after a
.I SKILL.md
edit; $/call is shown but flagged context-confounded.
Honors
.BR \-\-json .
.TP
.B \-\-plugins
Show
.B attribution_plugins
instead of
.B attribution_skills
(same column layout).
.TP
.B \-\-mcp
Show
.B attribution_mcp
\(em per-MCP-tool costs. A message's usage is split evenly across the MCP
tools it invokes, so totals stay comparable with the skills table.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Emit rows + outlier flag as JSON to stdout (parseable, no color codes).
Each row carries the token split
.RB ( in_tok ", " out_tok ", " cache_read ", " cache_create )
\(em the signal that separates \(lqskill talks too much\(rq (out-heavy)
from \(lqskill runs in fat sessions\(rq (cache_read-heavy).
Costs are priced per model: each per-model token bucket
.RB ( attribution_models ", "
schema v5) bills at its own tier rate (Opus, Sonnet, Haiku, Fable; cache_read
0.1\(mu, cache_create 1.25\(mu input). Pre-v5 / orphaned caches carry no
per-model split \(em their residual tokens fall back to the flat Sonnet rate.
.B meta.pricing
documents the rates and the residual fallback.
.RE
.TP
.B trends
Token-primary rolling 7-day chart: daily token bars (normalized to the busiest
day) with spend as a dim side column, a 30-day model split by tokens, busiest
day, average API duration per session, and the 7d-vs-30d token trend.
Reads from
.I ~/.cache/claudii/history-YYYY-MM.tsv
(written by the CC-Statusline handler).
Supports
.BR \-\-json .
Alias:
.BR t .
.TP
.B tokens
Token breakdown for the rolling window (default: 7 days), aggregated from the
JSONL transcripts under
.IR ~/.claude/projects .
Input+output is the primary figure; cache read/write and the cache-hit rate
.RB ( cache_read " / (" cache_read " + " cache_create " + " input ))
are shown alongside. Three sections:
.B By type
(throughput split across cache read / input / cache write / output, as share
bars),
.B By model
(a per-model matrix of input / output / cache rd / cache wr / hit), and
.B By day
(in+output per calendar day, bars normalized to the busiest day, with the
day-level hit rate). All three are floored to exactly
.I N
calendar days so the window matches the header.
.RS
.TP
.BI "\-\-days " N
Override the rolling window.
.RE
.TP
.B tools
Tool / efficiency lens over the rolling window (default: 7 days): a table of the
top tools by call count with share bars and per-tool error rate (a
.B \(rq
flag marks rates above 5%), the subagent types spawned, total thinking-block
volume, and a one-line callout of the highest-error-rate tool. The
throughput/reliability companion to
.B skills-cost
(which is cost-focused). MCP tool names are shortened to their tool segment and
the long tail is folded into a
.B +N more
line.
.RS
.TP
.BI "\-\-days " N
Override the rolling window.
.RE
.TP
.B limits
Rate-limit hits in the rolling window (default: 7 days) from the insights
.IR limit_hits .
Lists each hit (date, time, and the model that was running) newest-first, an
hour strip showing when hits cluster, and a per-model tally. Time and model only
\(em the data carries no percentage, and the 5h budget is account-wide, so the
model is \(lqwhat ran\(rq, not \(lqwhat is to blame\(rq. With no hits it reports
clear runway.
.RS
.TP
.BI "\-\-days " N
Override the rolling window.
.RE
.TP
.B cache
Prompt-cache hit rate per day and per model (default: 7-day window).
Aggregated from JSONL transcripts under
.IR ~/.claude/projects .
First run is slower (5\(en30 s) while the cache warms; subsequent runs
only re-aggregate changed sessions.
.RS
.TP
.BI "\-\-days " N
Override the rolling window.
.RE
.
.SS Configuration
.TP
.B config
Show all config values.
.TP
.BI "config get " key
Read a value using dot-notation.
Example:
.BR "claudii config get aliases.cl.model" .
.TP
.BI "config set " "key value"
Set a value.
Example:
.BR "claudii config set statusline.models opus,sonnet" .
.TP
.B "config reset"
Reset all config to defaults.
.TP
.BI "config export " "[file]"
Print config as JSON, or write to
.I file
if specified.
.TP
.BI "config import " file
Replace config with a JSON file (backs up existing config first).
.TP
.B "config theme"
List available color themes. Active theme marked with an asterisk.
.TP
.BI "config theme " name
Set the active theme.
Available:
.B default
(magenta accent, standard ANSI) and
.B pastel
(softer 256-color palette).
Stored as
.B theme.name
in
.IR config.json .
.TP
.B agents
List configured agents as a table with columns
.IR ALIAS ", " SKILL ", " MODEL ", " EFFORT ", " DESCRIPTION .
With no agents configured, shows onboarding instructions instead.
Supports
.BR \-\-json .
Configure via:
.RS
.nf
claudii config set agents.clorch.skill orchestrate
claudii config set agents.clorch.model opus
claudii config set agents.clorch.effort high
claudii config set agents.clorch.description "Orchestrator"
.fi
.RE
.
.SS Local LLM (omlx / gateii)
.TP
.B "omlx status"
Show whether the omlx segment is wired in, the
.I active.json
path, and oMLX server reachability.
.TP
.B "omlx connect"
Detect a gateii install, store the path, and probe the server.
.TP
.B "omlx test"
Render the cc-statusline against a synthetic
.I active.json
with the omlx segment.
.TP
.B "omlx disconnect"
Remove the
.B omlx
entry from any custom
.B statusline.lines
layout.
.PP
Override the
.I active.json
path via
.B CLAUDII_OMLX_ACTIVE
or config key
.BR statusline.omlx_active_path .
.
.SS VPN State (vpnii)
Shows the active WireGuard tunnel name in the cc-statusline and RPROMPT.
State file:
.IR ~/.cache/claudii/vpnii .
.B claudii vpnii
wraps write/clear with privilege drop so the file is always user-owned.
.PP
Recommended wg-quick config:
.PP
.RS
.EX
[Interface]
\&...
PostUp  = claudii vpnii set HomeLab
PreDown = claudii vpnii clear
.EE
.RE
.TP
.BI "vpnii set " "<name>"
Mark tunnel
.I name
as active.
Resolves the target user via
.B SUDO_USER
\(rA console owner \(rA
.B $USER
\(rA
.BR CLAUDII_USER .
.TP
.B "vpnii clear"
Remove the state file.
Aliases:
.BR "vpnii down" ", " "vpnii off" .
.TP
.B "vpnii show"
Print the current tunnel name, or
.I "no tunnel"
when none is set.
Alias:
.BR "vpnii status" .
.PP
Tailscale is detected separately via interface scan
(IPv4 in 100.64.0.0/10) and needs no state file.
.
.SS Activity Heatmap (vibemap)
Opt-in prompt-timing tracker, rendered as an ASCII heatmap.
Default
.BR off .
When enabled, the cc-statusline appends one TSV line per render to
.IR ~/.cache/claudii/vibemap.tsv .
Schema:
.BR "epoch \\\\t weekday \\\\t hour \\\\t minute \\\\t model \\\\t sid8 \\\\t delta_ms" .
No prompt content is recorded.
.TP
.B vibemap
Weekday \[mu] 3-hour-bin grid (default view).
Today\[aq]s weekday column is highlighted in accent color with a \[u25B6] prefix.
.TP
.BI "vibemap strip" " [--days N]"
Last
.I N
days \[mu] 24-hour strip (default 14, range 1\(en90).
Today\[aq]s row is highlighted with a \[u25B6] marker and a cursor at the current hour.
.TP
.B "vibemap status"
Show enabled state, file path, entry count, and oldest entry.
.TP
.B "vibemap path"
Print the vibemap file path.
.TP
.B "vibemap clear"
Remove the vibemap file.
.PP
Enable:
.BR "claudii config set vibemap.enabled true" .
.
.SS System
.TP
.BI "search " "['query']"
Launch Claude Code in the configured search directory
.RI ( search.dir ,
default:
.IR ~/claude-search ).
If a
.I query
is provided it is passed as the initial prompt.
.TP
.B restart
Reload the plugin by sourcing
.IR ~/.zshrc .
.TP
.B update
Update claudii.
Auto-detects Homebrew (runs
.BR "brew upgrade claudii" )
or git
.RB ( "git pull --ff-only" ).
Run
.B claudii restart
after updating.
.TP
.B version
Print version. When piped, prints the bare number only.
Supports
.BR \-\-json .
.TP
.B changelog
Release notes for the current version.
Alias:
.BR about .
.TP
.B doctor
Installation health check: Claude Code, jq, CC-Statusline config, cache directory,
completions, plugin load, cc-insomnii state, and version.
Supports
.BR \-\-json .
Alias:
.BR d .
.
