.SH CC-STATUSLINE SEGMENTS
Each segment is separated by a dim
.B \(bv
character and omitted when its data is absent.
The layout is controlled by
.B statusline.lines
(array of arrays; each inner array is one output line).
.PP
.TS
l l l.
Segment	Example	Description
_
model	\fBClaude Opus 4.8\fR	Model name (bold); effort level appended (ultracode/xhigh/max highlighted); \[u25B2] when thinking active
context-bar	\[u2588]\[u2588]\[u2588]\[u2588]\[u2588]\[u2591]\[u2591]\[u2591]\[u2591]\[u2591] 62% \[u26A1]73%	10-block bar + usable% + cache hit ratio
rate-5h	5h:17% \[u21BA]249m	5h rate limit + reset countdown (Pro/Max plans only)
rate-7d	7d:50% \[u21BA]3d15h	7d rate limit + reset countdown
cost	$0.42	Session cost in USD (cyan); omitted when zero
tokens	42.1K\(ua 8.3K\(da	Input / output tokens with K/M suffixes
lines-changed	+823 \-201	Git lines added (green) / removed (red); session total
duration	1h 23m	Wall-clock session duration (dim)
api-duration	api:45m	Time waiting for Claude API responses (dim)
burn-eta	ETA:180m	Estimated time until 5h limit exhausted (dim; requires >= 3 min session)
pace	\[u2191] / = / \[u2193]	Burn-pace tri-state vs linear: \[u2191] ahead (green), = on-pace (dim), \[u2193] behind (yellow). Opt-in only.
cron	\[u23F0] 42m	Time until next scheduled cron run (from Stop-hook session_crons). Opt-in only.
bg-tasks	\[u2699] 2bg	Number of background tasks pending (from Stop-hook bg_tasks). Opt-in only.
compactions	\[u267B]2	Compactions this session survived (detected via context-usage collapse). Opt-in only.
delta-5h	\[u03B4]5h:+12%	5h rate change since session start
delta-7d	\[u03B4]7d:+3%	7d rate change since session start
cache-create	\[u270E]1.2K	Tokens written into prompt cache this session
session-name	my-feature	Custom session name (from /rename or --name)
worktree	feat/login \[u23B7] main	Worktree + branch (dim)
dir	\[u2302] my-app	Working directory basename (dim)
github	\[u25C6] bmmmm/claudii #42	GitHub repo + active PR number (Claude Code 2.1.145+)
agent	@orc	Agent name prefixed @ (dim)
ruler	\(em\(em\(em\(em	Horizontal rule filling remaining terminal width
claude-status	Opus \[u2713]  Sonnet \[u2713]  Haiku \[u2713]	Model health from ClaudeStatus cache (auto-refreshes when older than status.cache_ttl)
clock	\[u263E] 23:30 +30m	Local time + bedtime nudge; delegates to \fBcc-insomnii\fR(1) when installed
.TE
.PP
.B context-bar color thresholds:
green < 70%, yellow 70\(en89%, red >= 90% (of usable context).
A dim
.B 1M
indicator is appended when the context window >= 1,000,000 tokens.
Cache hit ratio
.B \[u26A1]XX%
is shown when cache-read tokens are present (green >= 60%, yellow < 30%).
.PP
.B rate-5h / rate-7d:
color is cyan < 50%, yellow 50\(en79%, red >= 80%.
Set
.B statusline.rate_display
to
.B remaining
to flip percentages from "used" to "what's left"
(e.g.\&
.B 5h:62%
becomes
.BR 5h:38% ).
Color thresholds always key off the underlying usage.
.PP
.B clock:
when
.B cc-insomnii
is on
.B PATH
and
.B statusline.insomnii
is
.B auto
(default) or
.BR on ,
claudii pipes the upstream JSON to cc-insomnii and uses its output verbatim.
Set
.B statusline.insomnii
to
.B off
to suppress.
Bedtime forwarded as
.B CC_INSOMNII_BEDTIME
from
.B statusline.bedtime
(default
.IR 23:00 ).
.PP
.B cron / Stop-hook integration:
.B claudii-stop-hook
reads the Stop-hook JSON that Claude Code fires after every session turn and
extracts
.B session_crons
(array of scheduled tasks with a
.B next_run_at
timestamp) and
.B background_tasks
(sibling array).
The earliest
.B next_run_at
is persisted as
.B next_cron_at=<epoch>
in the per-session cache.
To enable, add
.B claudii-stop-hook
to the
.B hooks.Stop
array in
.IR ~/.claude/settings.json :
.PP
.RS
.EX
"hooks": {
  "Stop": [{ "type": "command", "command": "claudii-stop-hook" }]
}
.EE
.RE
.PP
The
.B cron
segment then renders
.B \[u23F0] <relative>
(e.g.\&
.BR "\[u23F0] 42m" )
when the epoch is in the future.
Not in the default layout \(em add
.B cron
to
.B statusline.lines
to opt in.
.B claudii se
also shows the glyph inline per session row when cached.
.PP
.B Terminal notifications (terminalSequence):
with
.B notifications.enabled
set to
.IR true ,
the hooks emit
.B terminalSequence
JSON (Claude Code \(>= 2.1.141) so the terminal shows alerts without a
controlling tty (works in tmux):
.B claudii-stop-hook
sets the window title when a monitored model is
.I down
(\fBnotifications.model_down\fR) and rings the bell when the cached burn-ETA
drops below
.B notifications.burn_eta_threshold_min
minutes (\fBnotifications.burn_eta\fR);
.B claudii-session-end-hook
(wire into
.BR hooks.SessionEnd )
sends a desktop notification with the session cost on real session
termination.
.B notifications.osc
picks the notify flavor:
.I 777
(Ghostty, urxvt, Warp) or
.I 9
(iTerm2, WezTerm, Windows Terminal).
.PP
.RS
.EX
"hooks": {
  "Stop":       [{ "type": "command", "command": "claudii-stop-hook" }],
  "SessionEnd": [{ "type": "command", "command": "claudii-session-end-hook" }]
}
.EE
.RE
.
.SH CONFIGURATION
User config:
.I ~/.config/claudii/config.json
(or
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/claudii/config.json
if set).
Created automatically from defaults on first run.
.PP
Key paths (dot-notation):
.PP
.TS
l l l.
Key	Default	Description
_
aliases.cl.model	sonnet	Model for \fBcl\fR
aliases.cl.effort	high	Effort for \fBcl\fR
aliases.clo.model	opus	Model for \fBclo\fR
aliases.clm.effort	xhigh	Effort for \fBclm\fR
aliases.clq.model	sonnet	Model for \fBclq\fR / search
fallback.enabled	true	Auto-fallback on outage
fallback.opus.model	sonnet	Fallback when opus is down
status.cache_ttl	300	Status cache TTL in seconds
display.timezone	(empty)	IANA timezone for absolute timestamps (e.g. Europe/Berlin); empty = system local
statusline.enabled	true	ClaudeStatus in RPROMPT
statusline.models	opus,sonnet,haiku	Models to monitor
statusline.lines	(5-line default)	CC-Statusline layout — array of segment-ID arrays
statusline.rate_display	used	Rate display: \fBused\fR or \fBremaining\fR
statusline.bedtime	23:00	Bedtime threshold (HH:MM, forwarded to cc-insomnii)
statusline.insomnii	auto	cc-insomnii delegation: \fBauto\fR/on/off
session-dashboard.enabled	off	Session Dashboard above prompt: on/off
notifications.enabled	false	terminalSequence alerts from hooks (master switch)
notifications.model_down	true	Window-title alert when a model is down
notifications.burn_eta	true	Bell + title when burn-ETA < threshold
notifications.burn_eta_threshold_min	30	Burn-ETA alert threshold (minutes)
notifications.session_end	true	Desktop notification on session end
notifications.osc	777	Notify flavor: \fB777\fR (Ghostty/urxvt/Warp) or \fB9\fR (iTerm2/WezTerm)
search.dir	~/claude-search	Directory for search mode
ui.spinner	random	Spinner style (random/beam/wave/dots/pulse/bounce/arc/orbit/ascii)
debug.level	off	Log level: off/error/warn/info/debug
vibemap.enabled	false	Opt-in activity tracking
vibemap.overview	true	Show Activity strip in claudii overview
overview.sections	account…commands	Overview section order + selection (array)
.TE
.
.SH STATUS CACHE
.I "${XDG_CACHE_HOME:-~/.cache}/claudii/status-models"
(override:
.BR CLAUDII_CACHE_DIR ).
Contains one line per model:
.PP
.RS
.nf
opus=ok
sonnet=down
haiku=ok
.fi
.RE
.PP
Refreshed automatically in the background when older than
.B status.cache_ttl
seconds.
.PP
Every state transition (e.g. opus ok\(->degraded) is appended to
.I status-history.tsv
in the same directory as a tab-separated line:
epoch, model, old state, new state.
The newest entries appear under \(lqRecent changes\(rq in
.BR "claudii status" ;
the log is trimmed to the newest 500 lines once it exceeds 1000.
.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CLAUDII_HOME
Path to the plugin directory. Set automatically.
.TP
.B CLAUDII_CACHE_DIR
Override the cache directory (default:
.IR ${XDG_CACHE_HOME:-~/.cache}/claudii ).
.TP
.B CLAUDII_FORCE_COLOR
Set to 1 to keep ANSI colors when stdout is not a terminal (e.g.\&
.BR "claudii se | less -R" ).
By default piped or redirected output is plain text.
.TP
.B CLAUDII_LOG_LEVEL
Override the debug log level (off, error, warn, info, debug).
.TP
.B CLAUDII_SPINNER_MODE
Override the spinner animation (takes precedence over
.BR ui.spinner ).
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Overrides the config directory (default:
.IR ~/.config ).
.TP
.B XDG_CACHE_HOME
Overrides the base cache directory (default:
.IR ~/.cache ).
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/claudii/config.json
User configuration.
.TP
.I $CLAUDII_HOME/config/defaults.json
Shipped defaults (read-only reference).
.TP
.I ~/.cache/claudii/status-models
Per-model status cache written by
.BR claudii-status .
.TP
.I ~/.cache/claudii/session-*
Per-session cache files written by the CC-Statusline handler
(model, context %, cost, rate-limit data).
.TP
.I ~/.cache/claudii/history-YYYY-MM.tsv
Persistent session history (Flight Recorder), rotated monthly.
One TSV line per CC-Statusline update: timestamp, model, cost, context %,
5h rate, session_id, input_tok, output_tok, api_duration_ms.
Read by
.BR "claudii trends" " and " "claudii cost" .
.TP
.I ~/.cache/claudii/vibemap.tsv
Opt-in activity log (written only when
.B vibemap.enabled
is true).
.TP
.I ~/.claude/settings.json
Claude Code settings, modified by
.BR "claudii cc-statusline" .
.
.SH VISUAL LANGUAGE
.PP
.TS
l l l.
Symbol	Meaning	Color
_
\(bu	active session	green
\(ci	ended / inactive	dim
\(tf	warning	yellow
\(mu	error / failure	red
\(OK	ok / success	green
\(da	down (model)	red
~	degraded	yellow
|	separator	\(em
\[u2588]	progress bar filled	context-sensitive
\[u2591]	progress bar empty	dim
.TE
.PP
Internal:
.B _claudii_sym
.RI ( lib/visual.sh )
accepts names
.RB ( active ", " inactive ", " warn ", " error ", " ok ", " down ", " degraded ", " sep )
and prints the colored symbol.
Constants:
.B CLAUDII_SYM_*
(symbols),
.B CLAUDII_CLR_*
(ANSI colors).
.
